$interpreted: Sophie: I was wondering why Rune got home so late...I never thought something like this would happen...
Deo: I didn't know Rune was part of a circus~
Deo: Now I know where I can find Rune.
Sophie: You're welcome anytime, it's just...
Sophie: We're a traveling circus, so I don't know how long we'll stay.
Deo: So you will leave the Desert Kingdom...
Sophie: Deo, was your father arrested?
Deo: Uh-huh. He did many bad things. When the Queen heard what he had done she was very upset.
Sophie: Her Highness, the Queen?
Sophie: That's right. Rune was set free by the Queen herself, so your father trying to buy and sell him was very disrespectful.
Deo: For the time being, Rune should be safe.
Sophie: ——What about you?
Sophie: Deo, if you have nowhere to go...
Sophie: would you want to join the circus?
Deo: I...
Deo: Even though my father will be away for a long time...
Deo: I think I ought to wait for him.
Sophie: (His father is such a scoundrel, but to this child...there's nothing that can replace him.)
Deo: And...and...
Deo: The slaves and workers at my home...I don't want to throw them out. I want to change their lives...
Sophie: You mean...?
Deo: I may be young, but I don't want to be like my father and treat the slaves so poorly.
Deo: I don't want to beat them or use them just to make money.
Deo: I'm not going to sell them to bad people and I'm going to improve their living conditions!
Deo: I want to help people, like Rune!
Sophie: But you're just a child. I'm worried about you...
Deo: Don't you worry. When I took my father to the authorities, there was a super cool general there who heard about what I was doing.
Deo: He said he'd try to help me!
Sophie: A "super cool" general?
Deo: He said that although I may be young, and the things I can do right now are limited, that I can do anything if I put my mind to it.
Deo: Even improve the lives of the slaves!
Sophie: ...Well since you've made up your mind, I'm sure you can do it!
Doofy Guard: Little Bossman!
Deo: They're here for me. Time to go home!
Deo: Rune! If one day you go to the other side of the ocean...you've got to tell me what adventures you go on!
Deo: I'll be waiting for you!
Rune: Rune...won't let you down.
Deo: Okay then, no lies~
Rune: Rune wouldn't lie to...Deo.
Deo: Rune, Sophie, we'll all go out and play one day!
Sophie: You got it!
Rune: Together...?
Sophie: We didn't see each other for just a day...but Rune has changed a lot.
Sophie: You look... a little bit lonely.
Rune: Rune has...changed?
Sophie: It's nothing! Let's go home! Ru-yi and them are waiting~
Rune: O...kay.
